title: Black Liberation & Palestine Solidarity - Augusta, GA 201302
description: On Wednesday, February 19, 2013, the CSRA Peace Alliance hosted a panel discussion entitled Black Liberation & Palestine Solidarity. For full details, visit http://csrapeace.org/2014/01/21/black-liberation-and-palestine-solidarity-panel-wed-feb-19-7pm/. This is an audio recording of the panelists, Lenni Brenner and Matthew Quest, discussing their book of the same title. Here how leaders of Black Liberation in the United States understood Zionism and Palestinian resistance and what lessons can be learned from the liberation struggles of African-Americans, European Jews and Palestinians. Almost 91 minutes long. Audio is mp3, and it is clear.
